Brightness proxy (comparative)

A stable “myth weight” score (not true magnitude):
B \propto \frac{(R^2 \cdot A)\cdot \text{phase}}{d^2}
	•	R: radius (Earth=1)
	•	A: albedo (rough)
	•	d: distance observer↔target
	•	phase: illumination fraction from geometry

